      "kind": "interview",
      "heading": "Bong Joon-ho on 'Mickey 17'",
      "guest": "Bong Joon-ho on",
      "note": "his first visit to the show since the Parasite run, with translator Sharon",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Mickey 17",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Adapted from the novel Mickey7. Bong says he passed on years of monster and sci-fi offers and took this one for the character, not the scale; Robert Pattinson was his first choice, cast off Good Time and The Lighthouse. He calls it one of his more hopeful films because he didn't want to destroy Mickey."
        },
        {
          "title": "Parasite",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Bong says he stayed calm through the Oscar run, then got the Mickey7 manuscript in June 2020 during the pandemic."
        },
        {
          "title": "Okja",
          "year": 2017,
          "note": "The Plan B connection that brought him the project, and his first VFX-creature collaboration with DP Darius Khondji."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Host",
          "year": 2006,
          "note": "Shot against real Seoul and the Han River, part of his habit of avoiding green screen."
        },
        {
          "title": "Snowpiercer",
          "year": 2013,
          "note": "The snowy-fields DNA reworked here as a spaceship rather than a train; John Hurt once called his method Hitchcockian."
        },
        {
          "title": "Memories of Murder",
          "year": 2003,
          "note": "Cited among his films where people eating together sets up explosive scenes."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Thing",
          "year": 1982,
          "note": "A lifelong John Carpenter influence rather than a direct Mickey 17 reference."
        },
        {
          "title": "Dances with Wolves",
          "year": 1990,
          "note": "A surprise touchstone: Bong studied its bison-herd sound for the creeper stampede."
        },
        {
          "title": "Assault on Precinct 13",
          "year": 1976,
          "note": "Bong's example of Carpenter's isolated-group-under-siege setup that he loves."
        },
        {
          "title": "Prince of Darkness",
          "year": 1987
        },
        {
          "title": "Good Time",
          "year": 2017,
          "note": "Where Bong first clocked Pattinson's range, via his friendship with the Safdies."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Lighthouse",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Bong rewatched it and saw 'Mickey 18' in Pattinson's performance."
        },
        {
          "title": "Armageddon Time",
          "year": 2022,
          "note": "The James Gray register Khondji usually prefers, far from VFX creatures."
